    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 1993 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) featuring the iconic 13B-REW twin-rotor powerplant. This example retains its original sequential twin-turbocharger configuration, delivering a seamless transition and robust boost pressure throughout the powerband. The chassis dynamics are sharp, benefiting from the factory front-midship layout and lightweight double-wishbone suspension. Recent maintenance includes a comprehensive refresh of the 'rat's nest' vacuum line assembly and a cooling system overhaul to ensure thermal stability. The five-speed manual transmission shifts precisely through all gates, paired with a responsive Torsen limited-slip differential. While the exterior shows minor age-appropriate patina, the drivetrain exhibits strong compression and linear power delivery, making this a prime candidate for the purist driver.",
      "price": 31500.0,
